The `<changes>` XML block works. It's the core mechanism I use to make precise and reliable modifications to your application's code. Think of it as a clear, machine-readable "plan" that I create for you, which the system then executes perfectly.

Here is a detailed breakdown of each part of the structure:

---

### The `<changes>` Block: The Root Element

```xml
<changes>
  ... all other tags go inside here ...
</changes>